article.description: Marcus Smart and Le'Bryan Nash scored 17 points each as Oklahoma State beat Tennessee 62-45 on Friday to move into the championship game at the Puerto Rico Tipoff.
article.shortLinkText: Oklahoma St. makes P.R. title game
article.headline: Marcus Smart, Le'Bryan Nash lead Oklahoma State past Tennessee
article.linkText: Oklahoma St. reaches title game in Puerto Rico

inlines.body:
Brennan: Oklahoma St. Looks Better

It's early, and Tennessee played poorly, but it's clear that Marcus Smart makes Oklahoma State a much better team, writes Eamonn Brennan. Blog

Puerto Rico Tip-Off

The 2012 Puerto Rico Tip-Off features teams like NC State, Tennessee and Providence battling for an early-season title. ESPN.com Topics has full coverage. Topics page »

article.story: BAYAMON, Puerto Rico -- Marcus Smart and Le'Bryan Nash scored 17 points each as Oklahoma State beat Tennessee 62-45 on Friday to move into the championship game at the Puerto Rico Tipoff. Smart, who also had nine rebounds, scored on a pair of layups and a 3-pointer during an 11-4 Cowboy run in the second half that put the game out of reach at 54-35 with under eight minutes to play. Markel Brown had 13 points for Oklahoma State (3-0). Trae Golden finished with 11 points for Tennessee (2-1). Oklahoma State will face No. 6 North Carolina State in the championship game while Tennessee takes on UMass.
